Even as other carmakers grapple with the outlook for their electrification plans, Volvo is keeping the pedal to the metal.
“No, we will not compromise on our electrification strategy,” Mårten Levenstam, the company’s head of strategy, told me earlier this month.
“We have a very good electrification strategy in place, and our suppliers see that we take this very seriously,” Buchhauser says.
Developing the battery systems internally enables engineers to customize the software for controlling the power systems and to collect data about their performance.
Battery heating and cooling are critical, as are the safety cells designed to protect battery packs in crashes and prevent them from catching fire.